---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<ServiceHero
  eyebrow="Lynx · Fire Magic · DCS · Twin Eagles · Kalamazoo · Wolf Outdoor"
  title="Outdoor Appliance Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle="Built-in grills, gas fireplaces, patio heaters, outdoor refrigerators. Same-day service across LA, Orange, Ventura, Riverside, San Bernardino. EPA 608 certified for refrigerant work."
  heroImageTitle="Outdoor Appliance Repair"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · What we do</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Outdoor living in Southern California is not a season. It's most of the year.</h2>

    <p>We service equipment that runs in November and runs in March because the weather is 68 degrees and there's no reason not to. That changes how outdoor appliances fail and how we work on them.</p>

    <p>The pattern we see across Beverly Hills, Bel Air, Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Newport Beach, and the Calabasas hillsides: built-in grills get used 6 to 8 months a year, gas fireplaces get used three months a year and then forgotten, patio heaters live outside year-round and corrode quietly. Each of these has its own typical failure mode. None of them are mysterious. Most are $200 to $600 fixes if you catch them before the part takes something else with it.</p>

    <p>We carry parts on the van for Lynx, Fire Magic, DCS, Twin Eagles, Alfresco, Kalamazoo, Wolf Outdoor, Viking Outdoor, Hestan, and Napoleon. Patio heater parts for Bromic, Infratech, and Fire Sense, including the thermocouples and igniters that fail most often. Gas fireplace parts for Heat & Glo, Heatilator, Majestic, and Valor. EPA 608 certification for the refrigerant work in built-in outdoor refrigerators and ice makers. BHGS #A49573.</p>

    <p>Outdoor appliances are not indoor appliances installed outside. The equipment is built differently. Sealed electrical compartments, gaskets rated for thermal cycling, condensers spec'd for 110°F ambient, brass burner hardware that resists corrosion, glass-ceramic surfaces with UV-stable bonding. The service approach is different too. We diagnose the install context (coastal salt aerosol, inland summer heat, garage exposure) before we diagnose the part, because the install context tells us what failed and what's about to fail next.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- COASTAL VS INLAND -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01.5 · Where you are matters</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Coastal and inland outdoor service run on different calendars.</h2>

    <p>The same Lynx grill running in Carbon Beach and the same Lynx grill running in Hidden Hills will show different failure patterns on different schedules. Coastal exposure (Malibu, Pacific Palisades, Newport Coast, Manhattan Beach) accelerates burner corrosion, igniter electrode oxidation, and condenser fouling on outdoor refrigerators. We recommend service every 6 months for coastal installations, vs. annually for inland.</p>

    <p>Inland properties (Hidden Hills, Calabasas, Beverly Hills proper, Pasadena foothills, Thousand Oaks, Conejo Valley) face a different stress profile. Summer ambient runs 95 to 105°F on July and August afternoons, which pushes outdoor refrigerator compressors to the upper end of their operating envelope. Year 4 to 6 is when condenser fan motors start failing on inland installs because they've been running at peak load every summer. We adjust service intervals based on your address. A Carbon Beach maintenance schedule is not the same as a Hidden Hills maintenance schedule.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- BRAND CATALOG -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01.7 · Brand catalog</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Brands we actually service, by category.</h2>

    <p><strong>Premium built-in grills:</strong> Lynx (Compton, CA), Fire Magic by RH Peterson (City of Industry, CA), DCS by Fisher & Paykel (Haier group), Twin Eagles (Camarillo, CA), Alfresco by BBQG, Kalamazoo Outdoor Gourmet (Michigan, hybrid charcoal-gas-wood units $15K+), Wolf Outdoor (Sub-Zero Group), Viking Outdoor (Middleby), Hestan, Napoleon, Bull Outdoor, Coyote, Capital, Lion. We don't service charcoal-only grills (Big Green Egg, Kamado Joe ceramic units) because the failure modes are masonry, not appliance.</p>

    <p><strong>Patio heaters:</strong> Bromic Heating (Australian, Tungsten and Platinum Smart-Heat lines), Infratech (American, dual-element and WD series), Schwank, AEI Sunpak, SunStar, Calcana, Fire Sense, AZ Patio Heaters, Hiland. Mounted electric infrared and freestanding propane both serviced.</p>

    <p><strong>Gas fireplaces:</strong> Heat & Glo, Heatilator, Majestic, Valor, Mendota, Lennox Hearth, Kingsman, Napoleon, Regency, Empire Comfort Systems. Direct-vent, vent-free, B-vent. We do not service wood-burning units (SCAQMD Rule 445 restrictions); we do gas conversions of existing wood-burning openings.</p>

    <p><strong>Outdoor refrigeration:</strong> Sub-Zero outdoor (UC-24RO, 424 series), U-Line outdoor collection, Perlick HC outdoor, Marvel outdoor, True Residential Outdoor TOR series, Lynx outdoor refrigerators, Hestan outdoor, Viking outdoor refrigerators, DCS outdoor refrigerators. EPA 608 Universal certification covers R-134a, R-290, and R-600a refrigerants used across this catalog.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 FIVE CATEGORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02 · What we service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Five outdoor categories we service.</h2>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Built-in Grills</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">Lynx, Fire Magic, DCS, Twin Eagles, Alfresco, Kalamazoo, Wolf, Viking, Hestan</p>
      <p>The most common failures we see on premium grills, in this order: igniter battery dead (the 9V in the battery tray that nobody knows about, on Lynx Professional E-series and Sedona), spark module failed, burners corroded through, regulator dropped pressure, gas valves stuck after long inactivity. A 2008-era Lynx Professional E36 with no spark on any zone is almost always the battery, $5 fix that gets diagnosed as a $400 ignition system replacement by techs who don't know the model. We see this every week.</p>
      <p class="cat-link"><a href="/outdoor/grill-repair/">See full grill service detail →</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Gas Fireplaces</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">Heat & Glo, Heatilator, Majestic, Valor, Mendota, Lennox Hearth, Kingsman</p>
      <p>In SoCal, gas fireplaces sit unused for 9 months a year and fail the first cold night in November. Most common: thermocouple oxidized after sitting (won't hold pilot), spider built a web in the pilot orifice (clogs gas flow), remote receiver lost battery charge, thermopile weak (can't drive valve). Honest field truth: 70% of "fireplace doesn't work" calls in October are one of these four issues. None of them are catastrophic. All of them are $150 to $350 repairs.</p>
      <p class="cat-link"><a href="/outdoor/fireplace-repair/">See full fireplace service detail →</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Patio Heaters</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">Bromic, Infratech, Fire Sense, AEI Sunpak, SunStar</p>
      <p>Permanent-mount patio heaters on Beverly Hills and Malibu patios run on natural gas plumbing. They live outside year-round, get rained on, and the thermocouple corrodes. The Bromic Tungsten BH8280036 thermocouple is a $36 to $80 part depending on supplier. Replacement takes 30 minutes. Customers who didn't know the part exists get told they need a new heater. We replace the thermocouple and the heater works for another 5 years.</p>
      <p class="cat-link"><a href="/outdoor/patio-heater-repair/">See full patio heater service detail →</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Outdoor Refrigerators & Ice Makers</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">Sub-Zero outdoor series, U-Line, Perlick, Lynx, Hestan, True residential outdoor, Viking outdoor</p>
      <p>Outdoor-rated refrigerators are not just regular fridges in a cabinet. They have sealed-system specifications, gasket compounds, and condenser placements built for high ambient temps and humidity swings. EPA 608 required for any refrigerant work, and we have it. Common failures: condenser fan motor seized after 4 to 6 years, door gasket compressed flat (won't seal in summer heat), evaporator drain blocked, compressor short-cycling on heat. We do not service supermarket multiplexed rack systems; those need a C-38 specialty contractor.</p>
      <p class="cat-link"><a href="/services/outdoor-refrigerator-repair/">See full outdoor refrigerator service detail →</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Outdoor Kitchen Components</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">Vent hoods, side burners, warming drawers, pizza ovens</p>
      <p>Side burners on built-in outdoor kitchens fail like residential cooktops: orifice blocked from cooking spillover, igniter clicks but no spark (battery), gas regulator at the line. Warming drawers (Wolf outdoor WWD30, Lynx LWD30) fail on element or controller. Pizza ovens (Mugnaini gas, Forno Bravo gas conversion, Ooni outdoor): we service the gas-fired models. We don't do new outdoor kitchen construction; we service what's installed.</p>
      <p class="cat-link"><a href="/outdoor/kitchen-repair/">See full outdoor kitchen service detail →</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02.5 BY CITY + MAINTENANCE + SPECIALIZED OUTDOOR COOKING -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02.5 · By city + maintenance</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">City-specific outdoor service pages, maintenance, and specialized cooking equipment.</h2>

    <p>Different SoCal addresses run different outdoor failure patterns — Newport Beach harbor properties don't fail the same way as Thousand Oaks hillside builds, and our city-specific pages carry the local context. Maintenance pages cover scheduled non-failure work — annual condenser servicing, gasket inspection, calibration before they break. Pizza ovens and smokers get their own pages because they're different equipment from grills with different failure modes.</p>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Outdoor Kitchen Repair by City</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">Built-in kitchen installations</p>
      <p>Custom outdoor kitchen builds run different appliance mixes by city — Newport Beach harbor-side installations get heavy salt-aerosol exposure, Thousand Oaks hillside builds run dust-load on condensers all summer. City-specific service pages with the local context:</p>
      <ul class="city-link-list">
        <li><a href="/outdoor/kitchen-repair-newport-beach/">Outdoor Kitchen Repair Newport Beach</a></li>
        <li><a href="/outdoor/kitchen-repair-thousand-oaks/">Outdoor Kitchen Repair Thousand Oaks</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Outdoor Grill Repair by City</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">Premium built-in grills</p>
      <p>Beverly Hills built-in grill installations skew Lynx Professional E-series and Wolf Outdoor with custom mason work — gated-property access and household-staff coordination matter:</p>
      <ul class="city-link-list">
        <li><a href="/outdoor/grill-repair-beverly-hills/">Outdoor Grill Repair Beverly Hills</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Outdoor Wine Cellar Repair by City</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">EPA 608 certified for refrigerant work</p>
      <p>Coastal and hillside estates run the most demanding outdoor wine cellar setups — salt aerosol on the Pacific Palisades and Newport Beach side, summer heat load on Bel Air ridge properties. WhisperKool, Sub-Zero outdoor wine, EuroCave, Vinotemp common across this address tier:</p>
      <ul class="city-link-list">
        <li><a href="/outdoor/wine-cellar-repair-pacific-palisades/">Wine Cellar Repair Pacific Palisades</a></li>
        <li><a href="/outdoor/wine-cellar-repair-newport-beach/">Wine Cellar Repair Newport Beach</a></li>
        <li><a href="/outdoor/wine-cellar-repair-bel-air/">Wine Cellar Repair Bel Air</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Outdoor Maintenance Services</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">Scheduled non-failure work</p>
      <p>For installs that haven't failed yet — preventive service before the part takes something else with it. Annual condenser cleaning, thermocouple inspection on the patio heaters, gasket compression check on outdoor refrigerators:</p>
      <ul class="city-link-list">
        <li><a href="/outdoor/kitchen-maintenance/">Outdoor Kitchen Maintenance</a></li>
        <li><a href="/outdoor/wine-cellar-maintenance/">Wine Cellar Maintenance</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="cat-block">
      <h3>Specialized Outdoor Cooking</h3>
      <p class="cat-brands">Pizza ovens · smokers — gas-fired models</p>
      <p>Different equipment from grills, different failure modes. Pizza ovens (Mugnaini, Forno Bravo, Ooni gas) and smokers (Traeger, gas-fired offset) get their own service pages because the diagnostic tree doesn't overlap with built-in grill work:</p>
      <ul class="city-link-list">
        <li><a href="/outdoor/pizza-oven-repair/">Outdoor Pizza Oven Repair</a></li>
        <li><a href="/outdoor/smoker-repair/">Outdoor Smoker Repair</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 REAL STORIES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent jobs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Real repair stories from the last few weeks.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Composite examples; model numbers, ages, and prices are accurate to typical scope.</p>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Beverly Hills · Lynx Professional E48 built-in, 2010 install</h3>
      <p>Owner called Tuesday morning, no spark on left zone. Tech checked battery in tray: dead. Replaced 9V (OEM 80489), spark restored. Total: $120 diagnostic, no parts charge, waived because the issue was the battery and we always waive when the fix is that small. Customer got 6 more years out of the grill.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Malibu · Bromic Tungsten Smart-Heat permanent gas heater, 2021 install</h3>
      <p>Five heaters across the patio, only one wouldn't light. Thermocouple BH8280036 oxidized from salt air. Replaced thermocouple, tested, working. Total: $120 diagnostic + $80 part + 30 min labor = $260 all-in. Customer asked about the other four and we did preventive thermocouple inspection on all of them. Three were within a season of failing. Replaced all preemptively.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Pacific Palisades · Heat & Glo SL-550TR direct-vent fireplace, 14 years old</h3>
      <p>Won't stay lit. Thermocouple test showed 12 mV (needs 18+ mV to hold valve). Replaced thermocouple and pilot generator together; they age together, and replacing one and not the other is a callback in 6 months. Tested pilot stable, main burner ignition, remote function. Total: $385.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Bel Air · Sub-Zero 424 outdoor refrigerator under-counter, 7 years old</h3>
      <p>Not cooling, ambient 92°F outside. Condenser fan motor seized, common at 5 to 7 years on outdoor units due to dust load. Replaced fan motor, cleaned condenser coil, tested. Pulldown to 38°F in 3 hours. Total: $620.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · What we don&apos;t do</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Honest scope. Knowing the boundary is part of being a real practitioner.</h2>

    <p>We don't do everything outdoor.</p>

    <ul class="scope-list">
      <li><strong>New outdoor kitchen construction.</strong> We service what's already built. For new builds we work with several outdoor kitchen contractors and can refer.</li>
      <li><strong>Wood-burning fireplaces or wood-fired ovens.</strong> SCAQMD Rule 445 restricts new wood-burning installations across most of LA, OC, Riverside, and San Bernardino. Most retrofits these days are gas conversions, and we do those.</li>
      <li><strong>Solar pool heating, outdoor pool equipment, spa equipment.</strong> Different trade. We refer.</li>
      <li><strong>Outdoor lighting, audio, irrigation.</strong> Different trades. We do appliances.</li>
      <li><strong>Supermarket multiplexed rack refrigeration with remote condensers.</strong> Specialty trade requiring C-38 license. We do reach-in and undercounter outdoor refrigerators only. For commercial walk-in cold storage see <a href="/commercial/refrigeration/">commercial refrigeration</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>This is not a weakness. Property managers and premium homeowners value contractors who know their limits and refer to the right specialist. Generic "we do everything outdoor" is marketing fiction.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 PRICING -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What outdoor appliance repair actually costs.</h2>

    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>What to expect</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Diagnostic visit</td><td>$120, waived with repair</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Most grill repairs</td><td>$200 to $600 (igniter, burner, regulator)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Major grill repair</td><td>$700 to $1,500 (manifold, multi-burner, sear zone)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Gas fireplace tune-up</td><td>$250 to $400 (thermocouple, pilot, cleaning)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Gas fireplace major repair</td><td>$400 to $900 (gas valve, control board, blower)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Patio heater repair</td><td>$200 to $450 (thermocouple, ignition, regulator)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Outdoor refrigerator repair</td><td>$350 to $900 (fan motor, gasket, control)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Outdoor refrigerator compressor</td><td>$1,200 to $2,200</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty on all repairs</td><td>90 days parts + labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="price-note">Prices reflect typical SoCal market. Premium brands (Kalamazoo, Hestan, Wolf outdoor) sometimes quote-based for parts-heavy jobs because OEM parts cost more. We tell you the cost before we start, never surprise you at the end.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 WHY US -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Why customers call us back</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Six reasons.</h2>

    <ul class="why-list">
      <li><strong>Parts on the van.</strong> We carry Lynx, Fire Magic, DCS, Bromic, Infratech, and common fireplace parts. 8 out of 10 jobs are one-visit fixes.</li>
      <li><strong>EPA 608 certified.</strong> Required for any refrigerant work in outdoor refrigerators and ice makers. Most outdoor-only contractors aren't. See our <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA certification page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Eight branches across SoCal.</strong> West Hollywood, Beverly Hills, LA, Pasadena, Thousand Oaks, Irvine, Rancho Cucamonga, Temecula. Same-day in most cases. Coverage map at <a href="/los-angeles-county/">LA County</a> and our other county hubs.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 and BBB Accredited.</strong> Both verifiable.</li>
      <li><strong>We won't sell you a replacement when a $50 part fixes it.</strong> Battery in the Lynx igniter, thermocouple in the Bromic heater, pilot generator in the fireplace. We're not on commission.</li>
      <li><strong>We service brands other shops won't touch.</strong> Kalamazoo, Hestan, custom outdoor kitchen builders' integrated systems. Most appliance shops decline because they don't carry parts. We do.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>If you're searching for indoor refrigerator repair instead, see our <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair/">residential refrigerator service</a>. Different page, different scope, $89 residential diagnostic.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 07 FAQ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">07 · FAQ</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Outdoor appliance repair, common questions.</h2>

